===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{Han compound|手|alt1=扌|包|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p}} – hold in one’s hands. Note that 包 has the meaning of “wrap”, hence connotations of “wrap in one’s hands, embrace”, thereby also making it an ideogrammic compound.

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*puʔ|t=to carry (on back or shoulders)}}. Cognate with {{och-l|保|to protect, rear}}, {{cog|mni|ꯄꯨ|t=to carry}}, {{cog|lus|pu|t=to carry (on the back / shoulders)}}, {{cog|my|ပိုး|t=to carry on the back, add onto}} (STEDT).

